Package: Jitterbox
Title: Make boxplots and stripplots by group 
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Brynley",
           family = "Hanson-Wright",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "brynhw@student.ubc.ca")
Description: This package includes the function `box.bygroup` used to make ggplots that 
    display the distribution of a quantiative variable within each group of a categorical 
    variable. It displays boxplots, stripplots, and means within each group to visualize 
    both raw data and summary statistics.
